reviews.review_text: Hot for '86 First set is quite good, nothing incredible but worth a checking out. "fire" is a bit shaky in its weird position but does some neat things. The show really picks up post space, Jerry playing lots of fast heavy chords. Bob's sweet summertime antics during Lovelight are funny but head scratching, which he acknowledges before US Blues, where they sing 'comin on' instead of 'come and gone' during the chorus! Box was then what everyone was waiting for, a most perfect ending. Good times. Good recording too.

Fire  In case anyone reading comments about this show because they are wondering why Fire On the mountain opened 2nd set is because the hill behind us was on fire. Small fire but still visible from stage was the smoke from the fire.
 As far as this recording goes it is surely a 4 out 5 star rating in my book. Has every member coming threw the tape.  Enjoy the show for what it's worth not judging it to years past makes this one a good quality to download.
